    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Wine while they climb, in Peney]]></title>
    <link href="http://playdegex.github.io/2010/09/wine-while-they-climb-in-peney/"/>
    <updated>2010-09-25T22:24:02+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://playdegex.github.io/2010/09/wine-while-they-climb-in-peney</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TJ5BQel1vnI/AAAAAAAAzYA/jjtOqCWSt8A/s1600/DSCN2575+%28Modified%29.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="clear: right; float: right; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 1em;"><img border="0" height="308" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TJ5BQel1vnI/AAAAAAAAzYA/jjtOqCWSt8A/s320/DSCN2575+%28Modified%29.JPG" width="320" /></a></div>


<p>The <a href="http://www.chateauvieux.ch/page.cfm?content=peney.cfm&amp;langue=en">Cafe at Peney</a>, near Satigny, has a public playground right outside. You can easily sip a glass of the local wine while your children play quite safely within this fenced-in playground.<br /><br />The playground itself includes a climbing frame in very good condition. There is also an &lsquo;eau potable&rsquo; fountain just outside the playground.</p>
